PRIVACY POLICY

Welcome to *Antigravity Brain Trainer* ("we", "our", or "us").
This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our mobile application.

---

 1. Information We Collect

 a) Personal Information

We **do not** require you to provide any personally identifiable information (like your email address or real name) to use the app. Any username you create for the leaderboard is stored strictly locally on your device.

 b) Game Data

We collect and store gameplay-related data locally on your device, including:

* Scores and performance
* Levels and progress
* Achievements and leaderboard rankings

 c) Device & Usage Information

We may collect non-personal analytics and crash data via third-party services to help improve the app:

* Device type and OS version
* App usage data (e.g., game starts, milestones reached)
* Crash logs and diagnostics

---

 2. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information to:

* Provide and maintain the game
* Save your progress and scores locally
* Enable local leaderboard functionality
* Improve gameplay experience
* Analyze performance and fix bugs

---

 3. Third-Party Services

We use third-party services to operate the app:

* Firebase (Analytics & Crashlytics for app stability and performance tracking)
* Google AdMob (advertising services)

These services may collect and process data according to their respective privacy policies.

---

 4. Advertising

Our app displays ads using Google AdMob.
AdMob may collect:

* Device identifiers
* Usage data

This helps in showing relevant advertisements.

Learn more: https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads

---

 5. Data Sharing

We do **not sell, trade, or rent** your personal information.

We only share non-personal analytics and crash data with:

* Service providers (Firebase, AdMob)
* Legal authorities (if required by law)

---

 6. Data Security

We use secure technologies and industry-standard practices to protect your data. Since your game data is stored locally on your device, its security largely depends on your device's security measures (e.g., screen locks, encryption).

---

 7. Children's Privacy

This app is suitable for users of all ages; however, we do not knowingly collect personal data from children under the age of 13, as no personal data is collected by the app itself.

If you believe a child has provided personal data to our third-party services, please contact us.

